







@(1-2=c3104.A.1) Say to my lord: This is what @wPN{Aradŋu}, your servant, says:

@(3-7=c3104.A.3) My lord, the vast territory which has been given to you as booty has been made obedient: it is of one mind. The people, abundant as vegetation, belong to @wRN{Šulgi}, shepherd of the reliable word. You are the god of mankind, in the south and the highlands. They keep their gaze fixed on you.

@(8-15=c3104.A.8) The widespread people, abundant as vegetation, say: @q[,Culgi]{“Hail, my lord!”}, from the flooding @wWN{Tigris} and @wWN{Euphrates} to the @wWN{Tigris} ……. …… will rise. …… put aside. …… I (?) will make. …… which is esteemed (?). When I have filled (?) ……,
